data.text: When Harold Lloyd Jenkins was born on 1 September 1933, in Friars Point, Coahoma, Mississippi, United States, his father, Floyd Dalton Jenkins, was 19 and his mother, Velma Lee McGinnis Jenkins, was 21. He married Ellen Matthews in 1953. He lived in Hendersonville, Sumner, Tennessee, United States for about 3 years and Gallatin, Sumner, Tennessee, United States in 2007. In 1955, his occupation is listed as american country music singer. He died on 5 June 1993, in Springfield, Greene, Missouri, United States, at the age of 59, and was buried in Sumner Memorial Gardens, Gallatin, Sumner, Tennessee, United States.
